# DECOHERE Project Rules for Cursor IDE

## Temporary Files
- Store all temporary, test, and backup files in the `temp_execution_files` directory
- This includes test outputs, logs, and any files not part of the main codebase
- Example: `os.path.join('temp_execution_files', 'output.csv')`

## Code Style
- Use snake_case for file names and function names
- Use CamelCase for class names
- Follow the existing code style in each file

## Documentation
- Document all functions and classes with docstrings
- Keep documentation in the `docs` directory up-to-date
- Update README files when making significant changes

## Testing
- Store test outputs in the `temp_execution_files` directory
- Run tests before committing changes
- Verify that the pipeline works correctly after changes

## Terminal Commands
- Limit output volume in terminal commands
- Use proper error handling in scripts
- Implement progress reporting for long-running operations

## Project Maintenance
- Periodically clean up the `temp_execution_files` directory
- Follow the guidelines in `docs/PROJECT_GUIDELINES.md` 